 18, 1963, page 3) under the photograph of King George V, Tsar Nicolas II, and his son, the Tsarevich. The inadvertent substitution of "Tovarich" for the last word is especially distressing in view of the fact that it was indeed a tovarishch ("comrade" in the Bolshevist sense) who a few years later was to murder the poor little boy.





Yours truly,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: AL LEVIN1

CC, 1 p.





Montreux, September 13, 1963

Palace Hotel

